"the output log file. (`#3630 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3630>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:771
msgid ""
"No longer raise ``AttributeError`` when legacy marks can't be stored in "
"functions. (`#3631 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3631>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:778
msgid ""
"The description above the example for ``@pytest.mark.skipif`` now better "
"matches the code. (`#3611 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3611>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:786
msgid ""
"Internal refactoring: removed unused ``CallSpec2tox ._globalid_args`` "
"attribute and ``metafunc`` parameter from ``CallSpec2.copy()``. (`#3598 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3598>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:790
msgid ""
"Silence usage of ``reduce`` warning in Python 2 (`#3609 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3609>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:793
msgid ""
"Fix usage of ``attr.ib`` deprecated ``convert`` parameter. (`#3653 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3653>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:798
msgid "pytest 3.6.2 (2018-06-20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:803
msgid ""
"Fix regression in ``Node.add_marker`` by extracting the mark object of a "
"``MarkDecorator``. (`#3555 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3555>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:807
msgid ""
"Warnings without ``location`` were reported as ``None``. This is corrected "
"to now report ``<undetermined location>``. (`#3563 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3563>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:811
msgid ""
"Continue to call finalizers in the stack when a finalizer in a former scope "
"raises an exception. (`#3569 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3569>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:815
msgid ""
"Fix encoding error with ``print`` statements in doctests (`#3583 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3583>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:822
msgid ""
"Add documentation for the ``--strict`` flag. (`#3549 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3549>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:829
msgid ""
"Update old quotation style to parens in fixture.rst documentation. (`#3525 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3525>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:832
msgid ""
"Improve display of hint about ``--fulltrace`` with ``KeyboardInterrupt``. "
"(`#3545 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3545>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:835
msgid ""
"pytest's testsuite is no longer runnable through ``python setup.py test`` -- "
"instead invoke ``pytest`` or ``tox`` directly. (`#3552 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3552>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:839
msgid ""
"Fix typo in documentation (`#3567 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3567>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:844
msgid "pytest 3.6.1 (2018-06-05)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:849
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug where stdout and stderr were logged twice by junitxml when a "
"test was marked xfail. (`#3491 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3491>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:853
msgid ""
"Fix ``usefixtures`` mark applyed to unittest tests by correctly "
"instantiating ``FixtureInfo``. (`#3498 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3498>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:857
msgid ""
"Fix assertion rewriter compatibility with libraries that monkey patch "
"``file`` objects. (`#3503 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3503>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:865
msgid ""
"Added a section on how to use fixtures as factories to the fixture "
"documentation. (`#3461 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3461>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:872
msgid ""
"Enable caching for pip/pre-commit in order to reduce build time on travis/"
"appveyor. (`#3502 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3502>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:876
msgid ""
"Switch pytest to the src/ layout as we already suggested it for good "
"practice - now we implement it as well. (`#3513 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/3513>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:880
msgid ""
"Fix if in tests to support 3.7.0b5, where a docstring handling in AST got "
"reverted. (`#3530 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3530>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:883
msgid ""
"Remove some python2.5 compatibility code. (`#3529 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/3529>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:888
msgid "pytest 3.6.0 (2018-05-23)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:893
msgid ""
"Revamp the internals of the ``pytest.mark`` implementation with correct per "
"node handling which fixes a number of long standing bugs caused by the old "
"design. This introduces new ``Node.iter_markers(name)`` and ``Node."
"get_closest_mark(name)`` APIs. Users are **strongly encouraged** to read the "
"`reasons for the revamp in the docs <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/mark."
"html#marker-revamp-and-iteration>`_, or jump over to details about `updating "
"existing code to use the new APIs <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/mark."
"html#updating-code>`_. (`#3317 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3317>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:903
msgid ""
"Now when ``@pytest.fixture`` is applied more than once to the same function "
"a ``ValueError`` is raised. This buggy behavior would cause surprising "
"problems and if was working for a test suite it was mostly by accident. "
"(`#2334 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2334>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:908
msgid ""
"Support for Python 3.7's builtin ``breakpoint()`` method, see `Using the "
"builtin breakpoint function <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/usage."
"html#breakpoint-builtin>`_ for details. (`#3180 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/3180>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:913
msgid ""
"``monkeypatch`` now supports a ``context()`` function which acts as a "
"context manager which undoes all patching done within the ``with`` block. "
"(`#3290 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3290>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:917
msgid ""
"The ``--pdb`` option now causes KeyboardInterrupt to enter the debugger, "
"instead of stopping the test session. On python 2.7, hitting CTRL+C again "
"exits the debugger. On python 3.2 and higher, use CTRL+D. (`#3299 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3299>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:922
msgid ""
"pytest not longer changes the log level of the root logger when the ``log-"
"level`` parameter has greater numeric value than that of the level of the "
"root logger, which makes it play better with custom logging configuration in "
"user code. (`#3307 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3307>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:931
msgid ""
"A rare race-condition which might result in corrupted ``.pyc`` files on "
"Windows has been hopefully solved. (`#3008 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/3008>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:935
msgid ""
"Also use iter_marker for discovering the marks applying for marker "
"expressions from the cli to avoid the bad data from the legacy mark storage. "
"(`#3441 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3441>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:939
msgid ""
"When showing diffs of failed assertions where the contents contain only "
"whitespace, escape them using ``repr()`` first to make it easy to spot the "
"differences. (`#3443 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3443>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:947
msgid ""
"Change documentation copyright year to a range which auto-updates itself "
"each time it is published. (`#3303 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3303>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:955
msgid ""
"``pytest`` now depends on the `python-atomicwrites <https://github.com/"
"untitaker/python-atomicwrites>`_ library. (`#3008 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/3008>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:959
msgid ""
"Update all pypi.python.org URLs to pypi.org. (`#3431 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3431>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:962
msgid ""
"Detect `pytest_` prefixed hooks using the internal plugin manager since "
"``pluggy`` is deprecating the ``implprefix`` argument to ``PluginManager``. "
"(`#3487 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3487>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:966
msgid ""
"Import ``Mapping`` and ``Sequence`` from ``_pytest.compat`` instead of "
"directly from ``collections`` in ``python_api.py::approx``. Add ``Mapping`` "
"to ``_pytest.compat``, import it from ``collections`` on python 2, but from "
"``collections.abc`` on Python 3 to avoid a ``DeprecationWarning`` on Python "
"3.7 or newer. (`#3497 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3497>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:974
msgid "pytest 3.5.1 (2018-04-23)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:980
msgid ""
"Reset ``sys.last_type``, ``sys.last_value`` and ``sys.last_traceback`` "
"before each test executes. Those attributes are added by pytest during the "
"test run to aid debugging, but were never reset so they would create a "
"leaking reference to the last failing test's frame which in turn could never "
"be reclaimed by the garbage collector. (`#2798 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/2798>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:987
msgid ""
"``pytest.raises`` now raises ``TypeError`` when receiving an unknown keyword "
"argument. (`#3348 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3348>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:990
msgid ""
"``pytest.raises`` now works with exception classes that look like iterables. "
"(`#3372 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3372>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:997
msgid ""
"Fix typo in ``caplog`` fixture documentation, which incorrectly identified "
"certain attributes as methods. (`#3406 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3406>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1005
msgid ""
"Added a more indicative error message when parametrizing a function whose "
"argument takes a default value. (`#3221 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/3221>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1009
msgid ""
"Remove internal ``_pytest.terminal.flatten`` function in favor of "
"``more_itertools.collapse``. (`#3330 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3330>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1013
msgid ""
"Import some modules from ``collections.abc`` instead of ``collections`` as "
"the former modules trigger ``DeprecationWarning`` in Python 3.7. (`#3339 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3339>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1017
msgid ""
"record_property is no longer experimental, removing the warnings was "
"forgotten. (`#3360 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3360>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1020
msgid ""
"Mention in documentation and CLI help that fixtures with leading ``_`` are "
"printed by ``pytest --fixtures`` only if the ``-v`` option is added. (`#3398 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3398>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1026
msgid "pytest 3.5.0 (2018-03-21)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1031
msgid ""
"``record_xml_property`` fixture is now deprecated in favor of the more "
"generic ``record_property``. (`#2770 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2770>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1035
msgid ""
"Defining ``pytest_plugins`` is now deprecated in non-top-level conftest.py "
"files, because they \"leak\" to the entire directory tree. `See the docs "
"<https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/deprecations.html#pytest-plugins-in-non-"
"top-level-conftest-files>`_ for the rationale behind this decision (`#3084 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3084>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1043
msgid ""
"New ``--show-capture`` command-line option that allows to specify how to "
"display captured output when tests fail: ``no``, ``stdout``, ``stderr``, "
"``log`` or ``all`` (the default). (`#1478 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/1478>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1048
msgid ""
"New ``--rootdir`` command-line option to override the rules for discovering "
"the root directory. See `customize <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/"
"customize.html>`_ in the documentation for details. (`#1642 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1642>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1053
msgid ""
"Fixtures are now instantiated based on their scopes, with higher-scoped "
"fixtures (such as ``session``) being instantiated first than lower-scoped "
"fixtures (such as ``function``). The relative order of fixtures of the same "
"scope is kept unchanged, based in their declaration order and their "
"dependencies. (`#2405 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2405>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1059
msgid ""
"``record_xml_property`` renamed to ``record_property`` and is now compatible "
"with xdist, markers and any reporter. ``record_xml_property`` name is now "
"deprecated. (`#2770 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2770>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1063
msgid ""
"New ``--nf``, ``--new-first`` options: run new tests first followed by the "
"rest of the tests, in both cases tests are also sorted by the file modified "
"time, with more recent files coming first. (`#3034 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3034>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1068
msgid ""
"New ``--last-failed-no-failures`` command-line option that allows to specify "
"the behavior of the cache plugin's ```--last-failed`` feature when no tests "
"failed in the last run (or no cache was found): ``none`` or ``all`` (the "
"default). (`#3139 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3139>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1073
msgid ""
"New ``--doctest-continue-on-failure`` command-line option to enable doctests "
"to show multiple failures for each snippet, instead of stopping at the first "
"failure. (`#3149 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3149>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1077
msgid ""
"Captured log messages are added to the ``<system-out>`` tag in the generated "
"junit xml file if the ``junit_logging`` ini option is set to ``system-out``. "
"If the value of this ini option is ``system-err``, the logs are written to "
"``<system-err>``. The default value for ``junit_logging`` is ``no``, meaning "
"captured logs are not written to the output file. (`#3156 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3156>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1084
msgid ""
"Allow the logging plugin to handle ``pytest_runtest_logstart`` and "
"``pytest_runtest_logfinish`` hooks when live logs are enabled. (`#3189 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3189>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1088
msgid ""
"Passing ``--log-cli-level`` in the command-line now automatically activates "
"live logging. (`#3190 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3190>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1091
msgid ""
"Add command line option ``--deselect`` to allow deselection of individual "
"tests at collection time. (`#3198 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3198>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1095
msgid ""
"Captured logs are printed before entering pdb. (`#3204 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3204>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1098
msgid ""
"Deselected item count is now shown before tests are run, e.g. ``collected X "
"items / Y deselected``. (`#3213 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3213>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1102
msgid ""
"The builtin module ``platform`` is now available for use in expressions in "
"``pytest.mark``. (`#3236 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3236>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1106
msgid ""
"The *short test summary info* section now is displayed after tracebacks and "
"warnings in the terminal. (`#3255 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3255>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1110
msgid ""
"New ``--verbosity`` flag to set verbosity level explicitly. (`#3296 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3296>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1113
msgid ""
"``pytest.approx`` now accepts comparing a numpy array with a scalar. (`#3312 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3312>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1120
msgid ""
"Suppress ``IOError`` when closing the temporary file used for capturing "
"streams in Python 2.7. (`#2370 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2370>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1124
msgid ""
"Fixed ``clear()`` method on ``caplog`` fixture which cleared ``records``, "
"but not the ``text`` property. (`#3297 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3297>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1128
msgid ""
"During test collection, when stdin is not allowed to be read, the "
"``DontReadFromStdin`` object still allow itself to be iterable and resolved "
"to an iterator without crashing. (`#3314 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/3314>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1137
msgid ""
"Added a `reference <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/reference.html>`_ page "
"to the docs. (`#1713 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1713>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1144
msgid ""
"Change minimum requirement of ``attrs`` to ``17.4.0``. (`#3228 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3228>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1147
msgid ""
"Renamed example directories so all tests pass when ran from the base "
"directory. (`#3245 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3245>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1150
msgid ""
"Internal ``mark.py`` module has been turned into a package. (`#3250 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3250>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1153
msgid ""
"``pytest`` now depends on the `more-itertools <https://github.com/erikrose/"
"more-itertools>`_ package. (`#3265 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3265>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1157
msgid ""
"Added warning when ``[pytest]`` section is used in a ``.cfg`` file passed "
"with ``-c`` (`#3268 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3268>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1160
msgid ""
"``nodeids`` can now be passed explicitly to ``FSCollector`` and ``Node`` "
"constructors. (`#3291 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3291>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1163
msgid ""
"Internal refactoring of ``FormattedExcinfo`` to use ``attrs`` facilities and "
"remove old support code for legacy Python versions. (`#3292 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3292>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1167
msgid ""
"Refactoring to unify how verbosity is handled internally. (`#3296 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3296>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1170
msgid ""
"Internal refactoring to better integrate with argparse. (`#3304 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3304>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1173
msgid ""
"Fix a python example when calling a fixture in doc/en/usage.rst (`#3308 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3308>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1178
msgid "pytest 3.4.2 (2018-03-04)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1183
msgid ""
"Removed progress information when capture option is ``no``. (`#3203 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3203>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1186
msgid ""
"Refactor check of bindir from ``exists`` to ``isdir``. (`#3241 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3241>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1189
msgid ""
"Fix ``TypeError`` issue when using ``approx`` with a ``Decimal`` value. "
"(`#3247 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3247>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1192
msgid ""
"Fix reference cycle generated when using the ``request`` fixture. (`#3249 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3249>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1195
msgid ""
"``[tool:pytest]`` sections in ``*.cfg`` files passed by the ``-c`` option "
"are now properly recognized. (`#3260 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3260>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1203
msgid ""
"Add logging plugin to plugins list. (`#3209 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/3209>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1210
msgid ""
"Fix minor typo in fixture.rst (`#3259 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3259>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1215
msgid "pytest 3.4.1 (2018-02-20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1220
msgid ""
"Move import of ``doctest.UnexpectedException`` to top-level to avoid "
"possible errors when using ``--pdb``. (`#1810 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/1810>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1224
msgid ""
"Added printing of captured stdout/stderr before entering pdb, and improved a "
"test which was giving false negatives about output capturing. (`#3052 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3052>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1228
msgid ""
"Fix ordering of tests using parametrized fixtures which can lead to fixtures "
"being created more than necessary. (`#3161 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/3161>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1232
msgid ""
"Fix bug where logging happening at hooks outside of \"test run\" hooks would "
"cause an internal error. (`#3184 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3184>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1236
msgid ""
"Detect arguments injected by ``unittest.mock.patch`` decorator correctly "
"when pypi ``mock.patch`` is installed and imported. (`#3206 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3206>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1240
msgid ""
"Errors shown when a ``pytest.raises()`` with ``match=`` fails are now "
"cleaner on what happened: When no exception was raised, the \"matching "
"'...'\" part got removed as it falsely implies that an exception was raised "
"but it didn't match. When a wrong exception was raised, it's now thrown "
"(like ``pytest.raised()`` without ``match=`` would) instead of complaining "
"about the unmatched text. (`#3222 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3222>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1248
msgid ""
"Fixed output capture handling in doctests on macOS. (`#985 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/985>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1255
msgid ""
"Add Sphinx parameter docs for ``match`` and ``message`` args to ``pytest."
"raises``. (`#3202 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3202>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1263
msgid ""
"pytest has changed the publication procedure and is now being published to "
"PyPI directly from Travis. (`#3060 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3060>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1267
msgid ""
"Rename ``ParameterSet._for_parameterize()`` to ``_for_parametrize()`` in "
"order to comply with the naming convention. (`#3166 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3166>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1271
msgid ""
"Skip failing pdb/doctest test on mac. (`#985 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/985>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1276
msgid "pytest 3.4.0 (2018-01-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1281
msgid ""
"All pytest classes now subclass ``object`` for better Python 2/3 "
"compatibility. This should not affect user code except in very rare edge "
"cases. (`#2147 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2147>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1289
msgid ""
"Introduce ``empty_parameter_set_mark`` ini option to select which mark to "
"apply when ``@pytest.mark.parametrize`` is given an empty set of parameters. "
"Valid options are ``skip`` (default) and ``xfail``. Note that it is planned "
"to change the default to ``xfail`` in future releases as this is considered "
"less error prone. (`#2527 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2527>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1296
msgid ""
"**Incompatible change**: after community feedback the `logging <https://docs."
"pytest.org/en/latest/logging.html>`_ functionality has undergone some "
"changes. Please consult the `logging documentation <https://docs.pytest.org/"
"en/latest/logging.html#incompatible-changes-in-pytest-3-4>`_ for details. "
"(`#3013 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3013>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1302
msgid ""
"Console output falls back to \"classic\" mode when capturing is disabled (``-"
"s``), otherwise the output gets garbled to the point of being useless. "
"(`#3038 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3038>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1306
msgid ""
"New `pytest_runtest_logfinish <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/"
"writing_plugins.html#_pytest.hookspec.pytest_runtest_logfinish>`_ hook which "
"is called when a test item has finished executing, analogous to "
"`pytest_runtest_logstart <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/writing_plugins."
"html#_pytest.hookspec.pytest_runtest_start>`_. (`#3101 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3101>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1313
msgid ""
"Improve performance when collecting tests using many fixtures. (`#3107 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3107>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1316
msgid ""
"New ``caplog.get_records(when)`` method which provides access to the "
"captured records for the ``\"setup\"``, ``\"call\"`` and ``\"teardown\"`` "
"testing stages. (`#3117 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3117>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1320
msgid ""
"New fixture ``record_xml_attribute`` that allows modifying and inserting "
"attributes on the ``<testcase>`` xml node in JUnit reports. (`#3130 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3130>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1324
msgid ""
"The default cache directory has been renamed from ``.cache`` to ``."
"pytest_cache`` after community feedback that the name ``.cache`` did not "
"make it clear that it was used by pytest. (`#3138 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/3138>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1329
msgid ""
"Colorize the levelname column in the live-log output. (`#3142 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3142>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1336
msgid ""
"Fix hanging pexpect test on MacOS by using flush() instead of wait(). "
"(`#2022 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2022>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1339
msgid ""
"Fix restoring Python state after in-process pytest runs with the "
"``pytester`` plugin; this may break tests using multiple inprocess pytest "
"runs if later ones depend on earlier ones leaking global interpreter "
"changes. (`#3016 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3016>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1344
msgid ""
"Fix skipping plugin reporting hook when test aborted before plugin setup "
"hook. (`#3074 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3074>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1347
msgid ""
"Fix progress percentage reported when tests fail during teardown. (`#3088 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3088>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1350
msgid ""
"**Incompatible change**: ``-o/--override`` option no longer eats all the "
"remaining options, which can lead to surprising behavior: for example, "
"``pytest -o foo=1 /path/to/test.py`` would fail because ``/path/to/test.py`` "
"would be considered as part of the ``-o`` command-line argument. One "
"consequence of this is that now multiple configuration overrides need "
"multiple ``-o`` flags: ``pytest -o foo=1 -o bar=2``. (`#3103 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3103>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1362
msgid ""
"Document hooks (defined with ``historic=True``) which cannot be used with "
"``hookwrapper=True``. (`#2423 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2423>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1366
msgid ""
"Clarify that warning capturing doesn't change the warning filter by default. "
"(`#2457 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2457>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1369
msgid ""
"Clarify a possible confusion when using pytest_fixture_setup with fixture "
"functions that return None. (`#2698 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2698>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1373
msgid ""
"Fix the wording of a sentence on doctest flags used in pytest. (`#3076 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3076>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1376
msgid ""
"Prefer ``https://*.readthedocs.io`` over ``http://*.rtfd.org`` for links in "
"the documentation. (`#3092 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3092>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1380
msgid ""
"Improve readability (wording, grammar) of Getting Started guide (`#3131 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3131>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1383
msgid ""
"Added note that calling pytest.main multiple times from the same process is "
"not recommended because of import caching. (`#3143 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3143>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1391
msgid ""
"Show a simple and easy error when keyword expressions trigger a syntax error "
"(for example, ``\"-k foo and import\"`` will show an error that you can not "
"use the ``import`` keyword in expressions). (`#2953 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2953>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1396
msgid ""
"Change parametrized automatic test id generation to use the ``__name__`` "
"attribute of functions instead of the fallback argument name plus counter. "
"(`#2976 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2976>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1400
msgid ""
"Replace py.std with stdlib imports. (`#3067 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/3067>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1403
msgid ""
"Corrected 'you' to 'your' in logging docs. (`#3129 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3129>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1408
msgid "pytest 3.3.2 (2017-12-25)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1413
msgid ""
"pytester: ignore files used to obtain current user metadata in the fd leak "
"detector. (`#2784 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2784>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1416
msgid ""
"Fix **memory leak** where objects returned by fixtures were never destructed "
"by the garbage collector. (`#2981 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2981>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1420
msgid ""
"Fix conversion of pyargs to filename to not convert symlinks on Python 2. "
"(`#2985 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2985>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1423
msgid ""
"``PYTEST_DONT_REWRITE`` is now checked for plugins too rather than only for "
"test modules. (`#2995 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2995>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1430
msgid ""
"Add clarifying note about behavior of multiple parametrized arguments "
"(`#3001 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3001>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1437
msgid ""
"Code cleanup. (`#3015 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3015>`_, "
"`#3021 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3021>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1440
msgid ""
"Clean up code by replacing imports and references of ``_ast`` to ``ast``. "
"(`#3018 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3018>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1445
msgid "pytest 3.3.1 (2017-12-05)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1450
msgid ""
"Fix issue about ``-p no:<plugin>`` having no effect. (`#2920 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2920>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1453
msgid ""
"Fix regression with warnings that contained non-strings in their arguments "
"in Python 2. (`#2956 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2956>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1456
msgid ""
"Always escape null bytes when setting ``PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST``. (`#2957 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2957>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1459
msgid ""
"Fix ``ZeroDivisionError`` when using the ``testmon`` plugin when no tests "
"were actually collected. (`#2971 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2971>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1463
msgid ""
"Bring back ``TerminalReporter.writer`` as an alias to ``TerminalReporter."
"_tw``. This alias was removed by accident in the ``3.3.0`` release. (`#2984 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2984>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1467
msgid ""
"The ``pytest-capturelog`` plugin is now also blacklisted, avoiding errors "
"when running pytest with it still installed. (`#3004 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3004>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1475
msgid ""
"Fix broken link to plugin ``pytest-localserver``. (`#2963 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2963>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1482
msgid ""
"Update github \"bugs\" link in ``CONTRIBUTING.rst`` (`#2949 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2949>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1487
msgid "pytest 3.3.0 (2017-11-23)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1492
msgid ""
"pytest no longer supports Python **2.6** and **3.3**. Those Python versions "
"are EOL for some time now and incur maintenance and compatibility costs on "
"the pytest core team, and following up with the rest of the community we "
"decided that they will no longer be supported starting on this version. "
"Users which still require those versions should pin pytest to ``<3.3``. "
"(`#2812 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2812>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1499
msgid ""
"Remove internal ``_preloadplugins()`` function. This removal is part of the "
"``pytest_namespace()`` hook deprecation. (`#2636 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/2636>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1503
msgid ""
"Internally change ``CallSpec2`` to have a list of marks instead of a broken "
"mapping of keywords. This removes the keywords attribute of the internal "
"``CallSpec2`` class. (`#2672 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2672>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1508
msgid ""
"Remove ParameterSet.deprecated_arg_dict - its not a public api and the lack "
"of the underscore was a naming error. (`#2675 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/2675>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1512
msgid ""
"Remove the internal multi-typed attribute ``Node._evalskip`` and replace it "
"with the boolean ``Node._skipped_by_mark``. (`#2767 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2767>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1516
msgid ""
"The ``params`` list passed to ``pytest.fixture`` is now for all effects "
"considered immutable and frozen at the moment of the ``pytest.fixture`` "
"call. Previously the list could be changed before the first invocation of "
"the fixture allowing for a form of dynamic parametrization (for example, "
"updated from command-line options), but this was an unwanted implementation "
"detail which complicated the internals and prevented some internal cleanup. "
"See issue `#2959 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2959>`_ for "
"details and a recommended workaround."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1527
msgid ""
"``pytest_fixture_post_finalizer`` hook can now receive a ``request`` "
"argument. (`#2124 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2124>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1530
msgid ""
"Replace the old introspection code in compat.py that determines the "
"available arguments of fixtures with inspect.signature on Python 3 and "
"funcsigs.signature on Python 2. This should respect ``__signature__`` "
"declarations on functions. (`#2267 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2267>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1536
msgid ""
"Report tests with global ``pytestmark`` variable only once. (`#2549 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2549>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1539
msgid ""
"Now pytest displays the total progress percentage while running tests. The "
"previous output style can be set by configuring the ``console_output_style`` "
"setting to ``classic``. (`#2657 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2657>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1543
msgid ""
"Match ``warns`` signature to ``raises`` by adding ``match`` keyword. (`#2708 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2708>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1546
msgid ""
"pytest now captures and displays output from the standard ``logging`` "
"module. The user can control the logging level to be captured by specifying "
"options in ``pytest.ini``, the command line and also during individual tests "
"using markers. Also, a ``caplog`` fixture is available that enables users to "
"test the captured log during specific tests (similar to ``capsys`` for "
"example). For more information, please see the `logging docs <https://docs."
"pytest.org/en/latest/logging.html>`_. This feature was introduced by merging "
"the popular `pytest-catchlog <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-catchlog/>`_ "
"plugin, thanks to `Thomas Hisch <https://github.com/thisch>`_. Be advised "
"that during the merging the backward compatibility interface with the "
"defunct ``pytest-capturelog`` has been dropped. (`#2794 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2794>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1559
msgid ""
"Add ``allow_module_level`` kwarg to ``pytest.skip()``, enabling to skip the "
"whole module. (`#2808 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2808>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1562
msgid ""
"Allow setting ``file_or_dir``, ``-c``, and ``-o`` in PYTEST_ADDOPTS. (`#2824 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2824>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1565
msgid ""
"Return stdout/stderr capture results as a ``namedtuple``, so ``out`` and "
"``err`` can be accessed by attribute. (`#2879 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/2879>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1569
msgid ""
"Add ``capfdbinary``, a version of ``capfd`` which returns bytes from "
"``readouterr()``. (`#2923 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2923>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1573
msgid ""
"Add ``capsysbinary`` a version of ``capsys`` which returns bytes from "
"``readouterr()``. (`#2934 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2934>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1577
msgid ""
"Implement feature to skip ``setup.py`` files when run with ``--doctest-"
"modules``. (`#502 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/502>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1585
msgid ""
"Resume output capturing after ``capsys/capfd.disabled()`` context manager. "
"(`#1993 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1993>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1588
msgid ""
"``pytest_fixture_setup`` and ``pytest_fixture_post_finalizer`` hooks are now "
"called for all ``conftest.py`` files. (`#2124 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/2124>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1592
msgid ""
"If an exception happens while loading a plugin, pytest no longer hides the "
"original traceback. In Python 2 it will show the original traceback with a "
"new message that explains in which plugin. In Python 3 it will show 2 "
"canonized exceptions, the original exception while loading the plugin in "
"addition to an exception that pytest throws about loading a plugin. (`#2491 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2491>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1599
msgid ""
"``capsys`` and ``capfd`` can now be used by other fixtures. (`#2709 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2709>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1602
msgid ""
"Internal ``pytester`` plugin properly encodes ``bytes`` arguments to "
"``utf-8``. (`#2738 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2738>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1605
msgid ""
"``testdir`` now uses use the same method used by ``tmpdir`` to create its "
"temporary directory. This changes the final structure of the ``testdir`` "
"directory slightly, but should not affect usage in normal scenarios and "
"avoids a number of potential problems. (`#2751 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/2751>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1611
msgid ""
"pytest no longer complains about warnings with unicode messages being non-"
"ascii compatible even for ascii-compatible messages. As a result of this, "
"warnings with unicode messages are converted first to an ascii "
"representation for safety. (`#2809 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2809>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1616
msgid ""
"Change return value of pytest command when ``--maxfail`` is reached from "
"``2`` (interrupted) to ``1`` (failed). (`#2845 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/2845>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1620
msgid ""
"Fix issue in assertion rewriting which could lead it to rewrite modules "
"which should not be rewritten. (`#2939 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2939>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1624
msgid ""
"Handle marks without description in ``pytest.ini``. (`#2942 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2942>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1631
msgid ""
"pytest now depends on `attrs <https://pypi.org/project/attrs/>`_ for "
"internal structures to ease code maintainability. (`#2641 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2641>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1635
msgid ""
"Refactored internal Python 2/3 compatibility code to use ``six``. (`#2642 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2642>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1638
msgid ""
"Stop vendoring ``pluggy`` - we're missing out on its latest changes for not "
"much benefit (`#2719 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2719>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1641
msgid ""
"Internal refactor: simplify ascii string escaping by using the "
"backslashreplace error handler in newer Python 3 versions. (`#2734 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2734>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1645
msgid ""
"Remove unnecessary mark evaluator in unittest plugin (`#2767 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2767>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1648
msgid ""
"Calls to ``Metafunc.addcall`` now emit a deprecation warning. This function "
"is scheduled to be removed in ``pytest-4.0``. (`#2876 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2876>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1652
msgid ""
"Internal move of the parameterset extraction to a more maintainable place. "
"(`#2877 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2877>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1655
msgid ""
"Internal refactoring to simplify scope node lookup. (`#2910 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2910>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1658
msgid ""
"Configure ``pytest`` to prevent pip from installing pytest in unsupported "
"Python versions. (`#2922 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2922>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1664
msgid "pytest 3.2.5 (2017-11-15)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1669
msgid ""
"Remove ``py<1.5`` restriction from ``pytest`` as this can cause version "
"conflicts in some installations. (`#2926 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/2926>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1675
msgid "pytest 3.2.4 (2017-11-13)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1680
msgid ""
"Fix the bug where running with ``--pyargs`` will result in items with empty "
"``parent.nodeid`` if run from a different root directory. (`#2775 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2775>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1684
msgid ""
"Fix issue with ``@pytest.parametrize`` if argnames was specified as keyword "
"arguments. (`#2819 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2819>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1687
msgid ""
"Strip whitespace from marker names when reading them from INI config. "
"(`#2856 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2856>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1690
msgid ""
"Show full context of doctest source in the pytest output, if the line number "
"of failed example in the docstring is < 9. (`#2882 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2882>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1694
msgid ""
"Match fixture paths against actual path segments in order to avoid matching "
"folders which share a prefix. (`#2836 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2836>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1700
msgid ""
"Introduce a dedicated section about conftest.py. (`#1505 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1505>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1703
msgid ""
"Explicitly mention ``xpass`` in the documentation of ``xfail``. (`#1997 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1997>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1706
msgid ""
"Append example for pytest.param in the example/parametrize document. (`#2658 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2658>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1709
msgid ""
"Clarify language of proposal for fixtures parameters (`#2893 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2893>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1712
msgid ""
"List python 3.6 in the documented supported versions in the getting started "
"document. (`#2903 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2903>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1715
msgid ""
"Clarify the documentation of available fixture scopes. (`#538 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/538>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1718
msgid ""
"Add documentation about the ``python -m pytest`` invocation adding the "
"current directory to sys.path. (`#911 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/911>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1724
msgid "pytest 3.2.3 (2017-10-03)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1729
msgid ""
"Fix crash in tab completion when no prefix is given. (`#2748 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2748>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1732
msgid ""
"The equality checking function (``__eq__``) of ``MarkDecorator`` returns "
"``False`` if one object is not an instance of ``MarkDecorator``. (`#2758 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2758>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1736
msgid ""
"When running ``pytest --fixtures-per-test``: don't crash if an item has no "
"_fixtureinfo attribute (e.g. doctests) (`#2788 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/2788>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1744
msgid ""
"In help text of ``-k`` option, add example of using ``not`` to not select "
"certain tests whose names match the provided expression. (`#1442 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1442>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1748
msgid ""
"Add note in ``parametrize.rst`` about calling ``metafunc.parametrize`` "
"multiple times. (`#1548 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1548>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1755
msgid ""
"Set ``xfail_strict=True`` in pytest's own test suite to catch expected "
"failures as soon as they start to pass. (`#2722 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/2722>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1759
msgid ""
"Fix typo in example of passing a callable to markers (in example/markers."
"rst) (`#2765 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2765>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1764
msgid "pytest 3.2.2 (2017-09-06)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1769
msgid ""
"Calling the deprecated ``request.getfuncargvalue()`` now shows the source of "
"the call. (`#2681 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2681>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1772
msgid ""
"Allow tests declared as ``@staticmethod`` to use fixtures. (`#2699 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2699>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1775
msgid ""
"Fixed edge-case during collection: attributes which raised ``pytest.fail`` "
"when accessed would abort the entire collection. (`#2707 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2707>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1779
msgid ""
"Fix ``ReprFuncArgs`` with mixed unicode and UTF-8 args. (`#2731 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2731>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1786
msgid ""
"In examples on working with custom markers, add examples demonstrating the "
"usage of ``pytest.mark.MARKER_NAME.with_args`` in comparison with ``pytest."
"mark.MARKER_NAME.__call__`` (`#2604 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2604>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1791
msgid ""
"In one of the simple examples, use ``pytest_collection_modifyitems()`` to "
"skip tests based on a command-line option, allowing its sharing while "
"preventing a user error when acessing ``pytest.config`` before the argument "
"parsing. (`#2653 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2653>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1800
msgid ""
"Fixed minor error in 'Good Practices/Manual Integration' code snippet. "
"(`#2691 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2691>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1803
msgid ""
"Fixed typo in goodpractices.rst. (`#2721 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/2721>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1806
msgid ""
"Improve user guidance regarding ``--resultlog`` deprecation. (`#2739 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2739>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1811
msgid "pytest 3.2.1 (2017-08-08)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1816
msgid ""
"Fixed small terminal glitch when collecting a single test item. (`#2579 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2579>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1819
msgid ""
"Correctly consider ``/`` as the file separator to automatically mark plugin "
"files for rewrite on Windows. (`#2591 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/"
"issues/2591>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1823
msgid ""
"Properly escape test names when setting ``PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST`` environment "
"variable. (`#2644 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2644>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1826
msgid ""
"Fix error on Windows and Python 3.6+ when ``sys.stdout`` has been replaced "
"with a stream-like object which does not implement the full ``io`` module "
"buffer protocol. In particular this affects ``pytest-xdist`` users on the "
"aforementioned platform. (`#2666 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/"
"issues/2666>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1836
msgid ""
"Explicitly document which pytest features work with ``unittest``. (`#2626 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2626>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1841
msgid "pytest 3.2.0 (2017-07-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1846
msgid ""
"``pytest.approx`` no longer supports ``>``, ``>=``, ``<`` and ``<=`` "
"operators to avoid surprising/inconsistent behavior. See `the approx docs "
"<https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/builtin.html#pytest.approx>`_ for more "
"information. (`#2003 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2003>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1851
msgid ""
"All old-style specific behavior in current classes in the pytest's API is "
"considered deprecated at this point and will be removed in a future release. "
"This affects Python 2 users only and in rare situations. (`#2147 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2147>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1856
msgid ""
"A deprecation warning is now raised when using marks for parameters in "
"``pytest.mark.parametrize``. Use ``pytest.param`` to apply marks to "
"parameters instead. (`#2427 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2427>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1864
msgid ""
"Add support for numpy arrays (and dicts) to approx. (`#1994 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1994>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1867
msgid ""
"Now test function objects have a ``pytestmark`` attribute containing a list "
"of marks applied directly to the test function, as opposed to marks "
"inherited from parent classes or modules. (`#2516 <https://github.com/"
"pytest- dev/pytest/issues/2516>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1872
msgid ""
"Collection ignores local virtualenvs by default; ``--collect-in-virtualenv`` "
"overrides this behavior. (`#2518 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/"
"issues/2518>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1876
msgid ""
"Allow class methods decorated as ``@staticmethod`` to be candidates for "
"collection as a test function. (Only for Python 2.7 and above. Python 2.6 "
"will still ignore static methods.) (`#2528 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/"
"pytest/issues/2528>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1881
msgid ""
"Introduce ``mark.with_args`` in order to allow passing functions/classes as "
"sole argument to marks. (`#2540 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/"
"issues/2540>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1885
msgid ""
"New ``cache_dir`` ini option: sets the directory where the contents of the "
"cache plugin are stored. Directory may be relative or absolute path: if "
"relative path, then directory is created relative to ``rootdir``, otherwise "
"it is used as is. Additionally path may contain environment variables which "
"are expanded during runtime. (`#2543 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/2543>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1891
msgid ""
"Introduce the ``PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST`` environment variable that is set with "
"the ``nodeid`` and stage (``setup``, ``call`` and ``teardown``) of the test "
"being currently executed. See the `documentation <https://docs.pytest.org/en/"
"latest/example/simple.html#pytest-current-test- environment-variable>`_ for "
"more info. (`#2583 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/issues/2583>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1898
msgid ""
"Introduced ``@pytest.mark.filterwarnings`` mark which allows overwriting the "
"warnings filter on a per test, class or module level. See the `docs <https://"
"docs.pytest.org/en/latest/warnings.html#pytest-mark- filterwarnings>`_ for "
"more information. (`#2598 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/"
"issues/2598>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1904
msgid ""
"``--last-failed`` now remembers forever when a test has failed and only "
"forgets it if it passes again. This makes it easy to fix a test suite by "
"selectively running files and fixing tests incrementally. (`#2621 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2621>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1909
msgid ""
"New ``pytest_report_collectionfinish`` hook which allows plugins to add "
"messages to the terminal reporting after collection has been finished "
"successfully. (`#2622 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2622>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1913
msgid ""
"Added support for `PEP-415's <https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0415/>`_ "
"``Exception.__suppress_context__``. Now if a ``raise exception from None`` "
"is caught by pytest, pytest will no longer chain the context in the test "
"report. The behavior now matches Python's traceback behavior. (`#2631 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2631>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1919
msgid ""
"Exceptions raised by ``pytest.fail``, ``pytest.skip`` and ``pytest.xfail`` "
"now subclass BaseException, making them harder to be caught unintentionally "
"by normal code. (`#580 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/580>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1927
msgid ""
"Set ``stdin`` to a closed ``PIPE`` in ``pytester.py.Testdir.popen()`` for "
"avoid unwanted interactive ``pdb`` (`#2023 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/"
"pytest/issues/2023>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1931
msgid ""
"Add missing ``encoding`` attribute to ``sys.std*`` streams when using "
"``capsys`` capture mode. (`#2375 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/"
"issues/2375>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1935
msgid ""
"Fix terminal color changing to black on Windows if ``colorama`` is imported "
"in a ``conftest.py`` file. (`#2510 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/"
"issues/2510>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1939
msgid ""
"Fix line number when reporting summary of skipped tests. (`#2548 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2548>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1942
msgid ""
"capture: ensure that EncodedFile.name is a string. (`#2555 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2555>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1945
msgid ""
"The options ``--fixtures`` and ``--fixtures-per-test`` will now keep "
"indentation within docstrings. (`#2574 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/"
"pytest/issues/2574>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1949
msgid ""
"doctests line numbers are now reported correctly, fixing `pytest-sugar#122 "
"<https://github.com/Frozenball/pytest-sugar/issues/122>`_. (`#2610 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2610>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1953
msgid ""
"Fix non-determinism in order of fixture collection. Adds new dependency "
"(ordereddict) for Python 2.6. (`#920 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/pytest/"
"issues/920>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1961
msgid ""
"Clarify ``pytest_configure`` hook call order. (`#2539 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2539>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1964
msgid ""
"Extend documentation for testing plugin code with the ``pytester`` plugin. "
"(`#971 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/971>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1971
msgid ""
"Update help message for ``--strict`` to make it clear it only deals with "
"unregistered markers, not warnings. (`#2444 <https://github.com/pytest- dev/"
"pytest/issues/2444>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1975
msgid ""
"Internal code move: move code for pytest.approx/pytest.raises to own files "
"in order to cut down the size of python.py (`#2489 <https://github.com/"
"pytest- dev/pytest/issues/2489>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1979
msgid ""
"Renamed the utility function ``_pytest.compat._escape_strings`` to "
"``_ascii_escaped`` to better communicate the function's purpose. (`#2533 "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2533>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1983
msgid ""
"Improve error message for CollectError with skip/skipif. (`#2546 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2546>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1986
msgid ""
"Emit warning about ``yield`` tests being deprecated only once per generator. "
"(`#2562 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2562>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1989
msgid ""
"Ensure final collected line doesn't include artifacts of previous write. "
"(`#2571 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2571>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1992
msgid ""
"Fixed all flake8 errors and warnings. (`#2581 <https://github.com/pytest- "
"dev/pytest/issues/2581>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1995
msgid ""
"Added ``fix-lint`` tox environment to run automatic pep8 fixes on the code. "
"(`#2582 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2582>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1998
msgid ""
"Turn warnings into errors in pytest's own test suite in order to catch "
"regressions due to deprecations more promptly. (`#2588 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2588>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2002
msgid ""
"Show multiple issue links in CHANGELOG entries. (`#2620 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2620>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2007
msgid "pytest 3.1.3 (2017-07-03)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2012
msgid ""
"Fix decode error in Python 2 for doctests in docstrings. (`#2434 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2434>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2015
msgid ""
"Exceptions raised during teardown by finalizers are now suppressed until all "
"finalizers are called, with the initial exception reraised. (`#2440 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2440>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2019
msgid ""
"Fix incorrect \"collected items\" report when specifying tests on the "
"command- line. (`#2464 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2464>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2022
msgid ""
"``deprecated_call`` in context-manager form now captures deprecation "
"warnings even if the same warning has already been raised. Also, "
"``deprecated_call`` will always produce the same error message (previously "
"it would produce different messages in context-manager vs. function-call "
"mode). (`#2469 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2469>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2028
msgid ""
"Fix issue where paths collected by pytest could have triple leading ``/`` "
"characters. (`#2475 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2475>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2031
msgid ""
"Fix internal error when trying to detect the start of a recursive traceback. "
"(`#2486 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2486>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2038
msgid ""
"Explicitly state for which hooks the calls stop after the first non-None "
"result. (`#2493 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2493>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2045
msgid ""
"Create invoke tasks for updating the vendored packages. (`#2474 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2474>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2048
msgid ""
"Update copyright dates in LICENSE, README.rst and in the documentation. "
"(`#2499 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2499>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2053
msgid "pytest 3.1.2 (2017-06-08)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2058
msgid ""
"Required options added via ``pytest_addoption`` will no longer prevent using "
"--help without passing them. (#1999)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2061
msgid "Respect ``python_files`` in assertion rewriting. (#2121)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2063
msgid ""
"Fix recursion error detection when frames in the traceback contain objects "
"that can't be compared (like ``numpy`` arrays). (#2459)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2066
msgid ""
"``UnicodeWarning`` is issued from the internal pytest warnings plugin only "
"when the message contains non-ascii unicode (Python 2 only). (#2463)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2069
msgid ""
"Added a workaround for Python 3.6 ``WindowsConsoleIO`` breaking due to "
"Pytests's ``FDCapture``. Other code using console handles might still be "
"affected by the very same issue and might require further workarounds/fixes, "
"i.e. ``colorama``. (#2467)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2078
msgid "Fix internal API links to ``pluggy`` objects. (#2331)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2080
msgid ""
"Make it clear that ``pytest.xfail`` stops test execution at the calling "
"point and improve overall flow of the ``skipping`` docs. (#810)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2085
msgid "pytest 3.1.1 (2017-05-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2090
msgid ""
"pytest warning capture no longer overrides existing warning filters. The "
"previous behaviour would override all filters and caused regressions in test "
"suites which configure warning filters to match their needs. Note that as a "
"side-effect of this is that ``DeprecationWarning`` and "
"``PendingDeprecationWarning`` are no longer shown by default. (#2430)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2096
msgid "Fix issue with non-ascii contents in doctest text files. (#2434)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2098
msgid "Fix encoding errors for unicode warnings in Python 2. (#2436)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2100
msgid ""
"``pytest.deprecated_call`` now captures ``PendingDeprecationWarning`` in "
"context manager form. (#2441)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2107
msgid "Addition of towncrier for changelog management. (#2390)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2111
msgid "3.1.0 (2017-05-22)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2115
msgid "New Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2117
msgid ""
"The ``pytest-warnings`` plugin has been integrated into the core and now "
"``pytest`` automatically captures and displays warnings at the end of the "
"test session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2122
msgid ""
"This feature may disrupt test suites which apply and treat warnings "
"themselves, and can be disabled in your ``pytest.ini``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2125
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = -p no:warnings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2130
msgid ""
"See the `warnings documentation page <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/"
"warnings.html>`_ for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2133
msgid "Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2135
msgid ""
"Added ``junit_suite_name`` ini option to specify root ``<testsuite>`` name "
"for JUnit XML reports (`#533`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2137
msgid ""
"Added an ini option ``doctest_encoding`` to specify which encoding to use "
"for doctest files. Thanks `@wheerd`_ for the PR (`#2101`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2140
msgid ""
"``pytest.warns`` now checks for subclass relationship rather than class "
"equality. Thanks `@lesteve`_ for the PR (`#2166`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2143
msgid ""
"``pytest.raises`` now asserts that the error message matches a text or regex "
"with the ``match`` keyword argument. Thanks `@Kriechi`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2146
msgid ""
"``pytest.param`` can be used to declare test parameter sets with marks and "
"test ids. Thanks `@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2151
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2153
msgid ""
"remove all internal uses of pytest_namespace hooks, this is to prepare the "
"removal of preloadconfig in pytest 4.0 Thanks to `@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2157
msgid ""
"pytest now warns when a callable ids raises in a parametrized test. Thanks "
"`@fogo`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2159
msgid ""
"It is now possible to skip test classes from being collected by setting a "
"``__test__`` attribute to ``False`` in the class body (`#2007`_). Thanks to "
"`@syre`_ for the report and `@lwm`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2163
msgid ""
"Change junitxml.py to produce reports that comply with Junitxml schema. If "
"the same test fails with failure in call and then errors in teardown we "
"split testcase element into two, one containing the error and the other the "
"failure. (`#2228`_) Thanks to `@kkoukiou`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2168
msgid ""
"Testcase reports with a ``url`` attribute will now properly write this to "
"junitxml. Thanks `@fushi`_ for the PR (`#1874`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2171
msgid ""
"Remove common items from dict comparison output when verbosity=1. Also "
"update the truncation message to make it clearer that pytest truncates all "
"assertion messages if verbosity < 2 (`#1512`_). Thanks `@mattduck`_ for the "
"PR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2176
msgid ""
"``--pdbcls`` no longer implies ``--pdb``. This makes it possible to use "
"``addopts=--pdbcls=module.SomeClass`` on ``pytest.ini``. Thanks "
"`@davidszotten`_ for the PR (`#1952`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2180
msgid ""
"fix `#2013`_: turn RecordedWarning into ``namedtuple``, to give it a "
"comprehensible repr while preventing unwarranted modification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2183
msgid ""
"fix `#2208`_: ensure an iteration limit for _pytest.compat.get_real_func. "
"Thanks `@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for the report and PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2186
msgid ""
"Hooks are now verified after collection is complete, rather than right after "
"loading installed plugins. This makes it easy to write hooks for plugins "
"which will be loaded during collection, for example using the "
"``pytest_plugins`` special variable (`#1821`_). Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2191
msgid ""
"Modify ``pytest_make_parametrize_id()`` hook to accept ``argname`` as an "
"additional parameter. Thanks `@unsignedint`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2195
msgid ""
"Add ``venv`` to the default ``norecursedirs`` setting. Thanks `@The-"
"Compiler`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2198
msgid ""
"``PluginManager.import_plugin`` now accepts unicode plugin names in Python "
"2. Thanks `@reutsharabani`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2201
msgid ""
"fix `#2308`_: When using both ``--lf`` and ``--ff``, only the last failed "
"tests are run. Thanks `@ojii`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2204
msgid ""
"Replace minor/patch level version numbers in the documentation with "
"placeholders. This significantly reduces change-noise as different "
"contributors regnerate the documentation on different platforms. Thanks "
"`@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2209
msgid ""
"fix `#2391`_: consider pytest_plugins on all plugin modules Thanks "
"`@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2216
msgid ""
"Fix ``AttributeError`` on ``sys.stdout.buffer`` / ``sys.stderr.buffer`` "
"while using ``capsys`` fixture in python 3. (`#1407`_). Thanks to "
"`@asottile`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2220
msgid ""
"Change capture.py's ``DontReadFromInput`` class to throw ``io."
"UnsupportedOperation`` errors rather than ValueErrors in the ``fileno`` "
"method (`#2276`_). Thanks `@metasyn`_ and `@vlad-dragos`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2224
msgid ""
"Fix exception formatting while importing modules when the exception message "
"contains non-ascii characters (`#2336`_). Thanks `@fabioz`_ for the report "
"and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2228
msgid ""
"Added documentation related to issue (`#1937`_) Thanks `@skylarjhdownes`_ "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2231
msgid ""
"Allow collecting files with any file extension as Python modules (`#2369`_). "
"Thanks `@Kodiologist`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2234
msgid ""
"Show the correct error message when collect \"parametrize\" func with wrong "
"args (`#2383`_). Thanks `@The-Compiler`_ for the report and `@robin0371`_ "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2279
msgid "3.0.7 (2017-03-14)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2282
msgid ""
"Fix issue in assertion rewriting breaking due to modules silently discarding "
"other modules when importing fails Notably, importing the ``anydbm`` module "
"is fixed. (`#2248`_). Thanks `@pfhayes`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2287
msgid ""
"junitxml: Fix problematic case where system-out tag occurred twice per "
"testcase element in the XML report. Thanks `@kkoukiou`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2290
msgid ""
"Fix regression, pytest now skips unittest correctly if run with ``--pdb`` "
"(`#2137`_). Thanks to `@gst`_ for the report and `@mbyt`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2293
msgid ""
"Ignore exceptions raised from descriptors (e.g. properties) during Python "
"test collection (`#2234`_). Thanks to `@bluetech`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2296
msgid ""
"``--override-ini`` now correctly overrides some fundamental options like "
"``python_files`` (`#2238`_). Thanks `@sirex`_ for the report and "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2299
msgid ""
"Replace ``raise StopIteration`` usages in the code by simple ``returns`` to "
"finish generators, in accordance to `PEP-479`_ (`#2160`_). Thanks "
"`@tgoodlet`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2302
msgid ""
"Fix internal errors when an unprintable ``AssertionError`` is raised inside "
"a test. Thanks `@omerhadari`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2305
msgid ""
"Skipping plugin now also works with test items generated by custom "
"collectors (`#2231`_). Thanks to `@vidartf`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2308
msgid ""
"Fix trailing whitespace in console output if no .ini file presented "
"(`#2281`_). Thanks `@fbjorn`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2310
msgid ""
"Conditionless ``xfail`` markers no longer rely on the underlying test item "
"being an instance of ``PyobjMixin``, and can therefore apply to tests not "
"collected by the built-in python test collector. Thanks `@barneygale`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2337
msgid "3.0.6 (2017-01-22)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2339
msgid ""
"pytest no longer generates ``PendingDeprecationWarning`` from its own "
"operations, which was introduced by mistake in version ``3.0.5`` (`#2118`_). "
"Thanks to `@nicoddemus`_ for the report and `@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2343
msgid ""
"pytest no longer recognizes coroutine functions as yield tests (`#2129`_). "
"Thanks to `@malinoff`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2346
msgid ""
"Plugins loaded by the ``PYTEST_PLUGINS`` environment variable are now "
"automatically considered for assertion rewriting (`#2185`_). Thanks "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2350
msgid ""
"Improve error message when pytest.warns fails (`#2150`_). The type(s) of the "
"expected warnings and the list of caught warnings is added to the error "
"message. Thanks `@lesteve`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2354
msgid ""
"Fix ``pytester`` internal plugin to work correctly with latest versions of "
"``zope.interface`` (`#1989`_). Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2357
msgid ""
"Assert statements of the ``pytester`` plugin again benefit from assertion "
"rewriting (`#1920`_). Thanks `@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for the report and "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2360
msgid ""
"Specifying tests with colons like ``test_foo.py::test_bar`` for tests in "
"subdirectories with ini configuration files now uses the correct ini file "
"(`#2148`_).  Thanks `@pelme`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2364
msgid ""
"Fail ``testdir.runpytest().assert_outcomes()`` explicitly if the pytest "
"terminal output it relies on is missing. Thanks to `@eli-b`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2385
msgid "3.0.5 (2016-12-05)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2387
msgid ""
"Add warning when not passing ``option=value`` correctly to ``-o/--override-"
"ini`` (`#2105`_). Also improved the help documentation. Thanks to "
"`@mbukatov`_ for the report and `@lwm`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2391
msgid ""
"Now ``--confcutdir`` and ``--junit-xml`` are properly validated if they are "
"directories and filenames, respectively (`#2089`_ and `#2078`_). Thanks to "
"`@lwm`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2394
msgid ""
"Add hint to error message hinting possible missing ``__init__.py`` "
"(`#478`_). Thanks `@DuncanBetts`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2396
msgid ""
"More accurately describe when fixture finalization occurs in documentation "
"(`#687`_). Thanks `@DuncanBetts`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2398
msgid ""
"Provide ``:ref:`` targets for ``recwarn.rst`` so we can use intersphinx "
"referencing. Thanks to `@dupuy`_ for the report and `@lwm`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2401
msgid ""
"In Python 2, use a simple ``+-`` ASCII string in the string representation "
"of ``pytest.approx`` (for example ``\"4 +- 4.0e-06\"``) because it is "
"brittle to handle that in different contexts and representations internally "
"in pytest which can result in bugs such as `#2111`_. In Python 3, the "
"representation still uses ``±`` (for example ``4 ± 4.0e-06``). Thanks "
"`@kerrick-lyft`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2406
msgid ""
"Using ``item.Function``, ``item.Module``, etc., is now issuing deprecation "
"warnings, prefer ``pytest.Function``, ``pytest.Module``, etc., instead "
"(`#2034`_). Thanks `@nmundar`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2410
msgid ""
"Fix error message using ``approx`` with complex numbers (`#2082`_). Thanks "
"`@adler-j`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2413
msgid ""
"Fixed false-positives warnings from assertion rewrite hook for modules "
"imported more than once by the ``pytest_plugins`` mechanism. Thanks "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2417
msgid ""
"Remove an internal cache which could cause hooks from ``conftest.py`` files "
"in sub-directories to be called in other directories incorrectly (`#2016`_). "
"Thanks `@d-b-w`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2421
msgid ""
"Remove internal code meant to support earlier Python 3 versions that "
"produced the side effect of leaving ``None`` in ``sys.modules`` when "
"expressions were evaluated by pytest (for example passing a condition as a "
"string to ``pytest.mark.skipif``)(`#2103`_). Thanks `@jaraco`_ for the "
"report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2426
msgid ""
"Cope gracefully with a .pyc file with no matching .py file (`#2038`_). "
"Thanks `@nedbat`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2454
msgid "3.0.4 (2016-11-09)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2456
msgid ""
"Import errors when collecting test modules now display the full traceback "
"(`#1976`_). Thanks `@cwitty`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2459
msgid ""
"Fix confusing command-line help message for custom options with two or more "
"``metavar`` properties (`#2004`_). Thanks `@okulynyak`_ and `@davehunt`_ for "
"the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2462
msgid ""
"When loading plugins, import errors which contain non-ascii messages are now "
"properly handled in Python 2 (`#1998`_). Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2465
msgid ""
"Fixed cyclic reference when ``pytest.raises`` is used in context-manager "
"form (`#1965`_). Also as a result of this fix, ``sys.exc_info()`` is left "
"empty in both context-manager and function call usages. Previously, ``sys."
"exc_info`` would contain the exception caught by the context manager, even "
"when the expected exception occurred. Thanks `@MSeifert04`_ for the report "
"and the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2471
msgid ""
"Fixed false-positives warnings from assertion rewrite hook for modules that "
"were rewritten but were later marked explicitly by ``pytest."
"register_assert_rewrite`` or implicitly as a plugin (`#2005`_). Thanks "
"`@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2476
msgid ""
"Report teardown output on test failure (`#442`_). Thanks `@matclab`_ for the "
"PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2479
msgid ""
"Fix teardown error message in generated xUnit XML. Thanks `@gdyuldin`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2482
msgid ""
"Properly handle exceptions in ``multiprocessing`` tasks (`#1984`_). Thanks "
"`@adborden`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2485
msgid ""
"Clean up unittest TestCase objects after tests are complete (`#1649`_). "
"Thanks `@d_b_w`_ for the report and PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2508
msgid "3.0.3 (2016-09-28)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2510
msgid ""
"The ``ids`` argument to ``parametrize`` again accepts ``unicode`` strings in "
"Python 2 (`#1905`_). Thanks `@philpep`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2514
msgid ""
"Assertions are now being rewritten for plugins in development mode (``pip "
"install -e``) (`#1934`_). Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2518
msgid ""
"Fix pkg_resources import error in Jython projects (`#1853`_). Thanks "
"`@raquel-ucl`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2521
msgid ""
"Got rid of ``AttributeError: 'Module' object has no attribute '_obj'`` "
"exception in Python 3 (`#1944`_). Thanks `@axil`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2525
msgid ""
"Explain a bad scope value passed to ``@fixture`` declarations or a "
"``MetaFunc.parametrize()`` call. Thanks `@tgoodlet`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2528
msgid ""
"This version includes ``pluggy-0.4.0``, which correctly handles "
"``VersionConflict`` errors in plugins (`#704`_). Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2549
msgid "3.0.2 (2016-09-01)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2551
msgid ""
"Improve error message when passing non-string ids to ``pytest.mark."
"parametrize`` (`#1857`_). Thanks `@okken`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2554
msgid ""
"Add ``buffer`` attribute to stdin stub class ``pytest.capture."
"DontReadFromInput`` Thanks `@joguSD`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2557
msgid ""
"Fix ``UnicodeEncodeError`` when string comparison with unicode has failed. "
"(`#1864`_) Thanks `@AiOO`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2560
msgid ""
"``pytest_plugins`` is now handled correctly if defined as a string (as "
"opposed as a sequence of strings) when modules are considered for assertion "
"rewriting. Due to this bug, much more modules were being rewritten than "
"necessary if a test suite uses ``pytest_plugins`` to load internal plugins "
"(`#1888`_). Thanks `@jaraco`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR "
"(`#1891`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2566
msgid ""
"Do not call tearDown and cleanups when running tests from ``unittest."
"TestCase`` subclasses with ``--pdb`` enabled. This allows proper post mortem "
"debugging for all applications which have significant logic in their "
"tearDown machinery (`#1890`_). Thanks `@mbyt`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2572
msgid ""
"Fix use of deprecated ``getfuncargvalue`` method in the internal doctest "
"plugin. Thanks `@ViviCoder`_ for the report (`#1898`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2589
msgid "3.0.1 (2016-08-23)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2591
msgid ""
"Fix regression when ``importorskip`` is used at module level (`#1822`_). "
"Thanks `@jaraco`_ and `@The-Compiler`_ for the report and `@nicoddemus`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2594
msgid ""
"Fix parametrization scope when session fixtures are used in conjunction with "
"normal parameters in the same call (`#1832`_). Thanks `@The-Compiler`_ for "
"the report, `@Kingdread`_ and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2598
msgid ""
"Fix internal error when parametrizing tests or fixtures using an empty "
"``ids`` argument (`#1849`_). Thanks `@OPpuolitaival`_ for the report and "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2601
msgid ""
"Fix loader error when running ``pytest`` embedded in a zipfile. Thanks "
"`@mbachry`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2615
msgid "3.0.0 (2016-08-18)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2617
msgid "**Incompatible changes**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2620
msgid ""
"A number of incompatible changes were made in this release, with the intent "
"of removing features deprecated for a long time or change existing behaviors "
"in order to make them less surprising/more useful."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2623
msgid ""
"Reinterpretation mode has now been removed.  Only plain and rewrite mode are "
"available, consequently the ``--assert=reinterp`` option is no longer "
"available.  This also means files imported from plugins or ``conftest.py`` "
"will not benefit from improved assertions by default, you should use "
"``pytest.register_assert_rewrite()`` to explicitly turn on assertion "
"rewriting for those files.  Thanks `@flub`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2631
msgid "The following deprecated commandline options were removed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2633
msgid "``--genscript``: no longer supported;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2634
msgid "``--no-assert``: use ``--assert=plain`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2635
msgid "``--nomagic``: use ``--assert=plain`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2636
msgid "``--report``: use ``-r`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2638
msgid "Thanks to `@RedBeardCode`_ for the PR (`#1664`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2640
msgid ""
"ImportErrors in plugins now are a fatal error instead of issuing a pytest "
"warning (`#1479`_). Thanks to `@The-Compiler`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2643
msgid "Removed support code for Python 3 versions < 3.3 (`#1627`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2645
msgid ""
"Removed all ``py.test-X*`` entry points. The versioned, suffixed entry "
"points were never documented and a leftover from a pre-virtualenv era. These "
"entry points also created broken entry points in wheels, so removing them "
"also removes a source of confusion for users (`#1632`_). Thanks "
"`@obestwalter`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2651
msgid ""
"``pytest.skip()`` now raises an error when used to decorate a test function, "
"as opposed to its original intent (to imperatively skip a test inside a test "
"function). Previously this usage would cause the entire module to be skipped "
"(`#607`_). Thanks `@omarkohl`_ for the complete PR (`#1519`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2656
msgid ""
"Exit tests if a collection error occurs. A poll indicated most users will "
"hit CTRL-C anyway as soon as they see collection errors, so pytest might as "
"well make that the default behavior (`#1421`_). A ``--continue-on-collection-"
"errors`` option has been added to restore the previous behaviour. Thanks "
"`@olegpidsadnyi`_ and `@omarkohl`_ for the complete PR (`#1628`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2661
msgid ""
"Renamed the pytest ``pdb`` module (plugin) into ``debugging`` to avoid "
"clashes with the builtin ``pdb`` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2663
msgid ""
"Raise a helpful failure message when requesting a parametrized fixture at "
"runtime, e.g. with ``request.getfixturevalue``. Previously these parameters "
"were simply never defined, so a fixture decorated like ``@pytest."
"fixture(params=[0, 1, 2])`` only ran once (`#460`_). Thanks to `@nikratio`_ "
"for the bug report, `@RedBeardCode`_ and `@tomviner`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2669
msgid ""
"``_pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch`` class has been renamed to ``_pytest."
"monkeypatch.MonkeyPatch`` so it doesn't conflict with the ``monkeypatch`` "
"fixture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2672
msgid ""
"``--exitfirst / -x`` can now be overridden by a following ``--maxfail=N`` "
"and is just a synonym for ``--maxfail=1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2676 ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3118
msgid "**New Features**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2678
msgid ""
"Support nose-style ``__test__`` attribute on methods of classes, including "
"unittest-style Classes. If set to ``False``, the test will not be collected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2682
msgid ""
"New ``doctest_namespace`` fixture for injecting names into the namespace in "
"which doctests run. Thanks `@milliams`_ for the complete PR (`#1428`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2686
msgid ""
"New ``--doctest-report`` option available to change the output format of "
"diffs when running (failing) doctests (implements `#1749`_). Thanks "
"`@hartym`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2690
msgid ""
"New ``name`` argument to ``pytest.fixture`` decorator which allows a custom "
"name for a fixture (to solve the funcarg-shadowing-fixture problem). Thanks "
"`@novas0x2a`_ for the complete PR (`#1444`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2694
msgid ""
"New ``approx()`` function for easily comparing floating-point numbers in "
"tests. Thanks `@kalekundert`_ for the complete PR (`#1441`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2698
msgid ""
"Ability to add global properties in the final xunit output file by accessing "
"the internal ``junitxml`` plugin (experimental). Thanks `@tareqalayan`_ for "
"the complete PR `#1454`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2702
msgid ""
"New ``ExceptionInfo.match()`` method to match a regular expression on the "
"string representation of an exception (`#372`_). Thanks `@omarkohl`_ for the "
"complete PR (`#1502`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2706
msgid ""
"``__tracebackhide__`` can now also be set to a callable which then can "
"decide whether to filter the traceback based on the ``ExceptionInfo`` object "
"passed to it. Thanks `@The-Compiler`_ for the complete PR (`#1526`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2710
msgid ""
"New ``pytest_make_parametrize_id(config, val)`` hook which can be used by "
"plugins to provide friendly strings for custom types. Thanks `@palaviv`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2714
msgid ""
"``capsys`` and ``capfd`` now have a ``disabled()`` context-manager method, "
"which can be used to temporarily disable capture within a test. Thanks "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2718
msgid ""
"New cli flag ``--fixtures-per-test``: shows which fixtures are being used "
"for each selected test item. Features doc strings of fixtures by default. "
"Can also show where fixtures are defined if combined with ``-v``. Thanks "
"`@hackebrot`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2723
msgid ""
"Introduce ``pytest`` command as recommended entry point. Note that ``py."
"test`` still works and is not scheduled for removal. Closes proposal "
"`#1629`_. Thanks `@obestwalter`_ and `@davehunt`_ for the complete PR "
"(`#1633`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2728
msgid "New cli flags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2730
msgid ""
"``--setup-plan``: performs normal collection and reports the potential setup "
"and teardown and does not execute any fixtures and tests;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2732
msgid ""
"``--setup-only``: performs normal collection, executes setup and teardown of "
"fixtures and reports them;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2734
msgid ""
"``--setup-show``: performs normal test execution and additionally shows "
"setup and teardown of fixtures;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2736
msgid ""
"``--keep-duplicates``: py.test now ignores duplicated paths given in the "
"command line. To retain the previous behavior where the same test could be "
"run multiple times by specifying it in the command-line multiple times, pass "
"the ``--keep-duplicates`` argument (`#1609`_);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2741
msgid ""
"Thanks `@d6e`_, `@kvas-it`_, `@sallner`_, `@ioggstream`_ and `@omarkohl`_ "
"for the PRs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2743
msgid ""
"New CLI flag ``--override-ini``/``-o``: overrides values from the ini file. "
"For example: ``\"-o xfail_strict=True\"``'. Thanks `@blueyed`_ and "
"`@fengxx`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2747
msgid "New hooks:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2749
msgid "``pytest_fixture_setup(fixturedef, request)``: executes fixture setup;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2750
msgid ""
"``pytest_fixture_post_finalizer(fixturedef)``: called after the fixture's "
"finalizer and has access to the fixture's result cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2753
msgid "Thanks `@d6e`_, `@sallner`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2755
msgid ""
"Issue warnings for asserts whose test is a tuple literal. Such asserts will "
"never fail because tuples are always truthy and are usually a mistake (see "
"`#1562`_). Thanks `@kvas-it`_, for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2759
msgid ""
"Allow passing a custom debugger class (e.g. ``--pdbcls=IPython.core.debugger:"
"Pdb``). Thanks to `@anntzer`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2763 ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3149
msgid "**Changes**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2765
msgid ""
"Plugins now benefit from assertion rewriting.  Thanks `@sober7`_, "
"`@nicoddemus`_ and `@flub`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2768
msgid ""
"Change ``report.outcome`` for ``xpassed`` tests to ``\"passed\"`` in non-"
"strict mode and ``\"failed\"`` in strict mode. Thanks to `@hackebrot`_ for "
"the PR (`#1795`_) and `@gprasad84`_ for report (`#1546`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2772
msgid ""
"Tests marked with ``xfail(strict=False)`` (the default) now appear in "
"JUnitXML reports as passing tests instead of skipped. Thanks to "
"`@hackebrot`_ for the PR (`#1795`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2776
msgid ""
"Highlight path of the file location in the error report to make it easier to "
"copy/paste. Thanks `@suzaku`_ for the PR (`#1778`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2779
msgid ""
"Fixtures marked with ``@pytest.fixture`` can now use ``yield`` statements "
"exactly like those marked with the ``@pytest.yield_fixture`` decorator. This "
"change renders ``@pytest.yield_fixture`` deprecated and makes ``@pytest."
"fixture`` with ``yield`` statements the preferred way to write teardown code "
"(`#1461`_). Thanks `@csaftoiu`_ for bringing this to attention and "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2785
msgid ""
"Explicitly passed parametrize ids do not get escaped to ascii (`#1351`_). "
"Thanks `@ceridwen`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2788
msgid ""
"Fixtures are now sorted in the error message displayed when an unknown "
"fixture is declared in a test function. Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2792
msgid ""
"``pytest_terminal_summary`` hook now receives the ``exitstatus`` of the test "
"session as argument. Thanks `@blueyed`_ for the PR (`#1809`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2795
msgid ""
"Parametrize ids can accept ``None`` as specific test id, in which case the "
"automatically generated id for that argument will be used. Thanks "
"`@palaviv`_ for the complete PR (`#1468`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2799
msgid ""
"The parameter to xunit-style setup/teardown methods (``setup_method``, "
"``setup_module``, etc.) is now optional and may be omitted. Thanks `@okken`_ "
"for bringing this to attention and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2803
msgid ""
"Improved automatic id generation selection in case of duplicate ids in "
"parametrize. Thanks `@palaviv`_ for the complete PR (`#1474`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2807
msgid ""
"Now pytest warnings summary is shown up by default. Added a new flag ``--"
"disable-pytest-warnings`` to explicitly disable the warnings summary "
"(`#1668`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2810
msgid ""
"Make ImportError during collection more explicit by reminding the user to "
"check the name of the test module/package(s) (`#1426`_). Thanks `@omarkohl`_ "
"for the complete PR (`#1520`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2814
msgid ""
"Add ``build/`` and ``dist/`` to the default ``--norecursedirs`` list. Thanks "
"`@mikofski`_ for the report and `@tomviner`_ for the PR (`#1544`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2817
msgid ""
"``pytest.raises`` in the context manager form accepts a custom ``message`` "
"to raise when no exception occurred. Thanks `@palaviv`_ for the complete PR "
"(`#1616`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2821
msgid ""
"``conftest.py`` files now benefit from assertion rewriting; previously it "
"was only available for test modules. Thanks `@flub`_, `@sober7`_ and "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR (`#1619`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2825 ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2920
msgid ""
"Text documents without any doctests no longer appear as \"skipped\". Thanks "
"`@graingert`_ for reporting and providing a full PR (`#1580`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2828
msgid ""
"Ensure that a module within a namespace package can be found when it is "
"specified on the command line together with the ``--pyargs`` option.  Thanks "
"to `@taschini`_ for the PR (`#1597`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2832
msgid ""
"Always include full assertion explanation during assertion rewriting. The "
"previous behaviour was hiding sub-expressions that happened to be ``False``, "
"assuming this was redundant information. Thanks `@bagerard`_ for reporting "
"(`#1503`_). Thanks to `@davehunt`_ and `@tomviner`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2837
msgid ""
"``OptionGroup.addoption()`` now checks if option names were already added "
"before, to make it easier to track down issues like `#1618`_. Before, you "
"only got exceptions later from ``argparse`` library, giving no clue about "
"the actual reason for double-added options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2842
msgid ""
"``yield``-based tests are considered deprecated and will be removed in "
"pytest-4.0. Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2845
msgid ""
"``[pytest]`` sections in ``setup.cfg`` files should now be named ``[tool:"
"pytest]`` to avoid conflicts with other distutils commands (see `#567`_). "
"``[pytest]`` sections in ``pytest.ini`` or ``tox.ini`` files are supported "
"and unchanged. Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2850
msgid ""
"Using ``pytest_funcarg__`` prefix to declare fixtures is considered "
"deprecated and will be removed in pytest-4.0 (`#1684`_). Thanks "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2854
msgid ""
"Passing a command-line string to ``pytest.main()`` is considered deprecated "
"and scheduled for removal in pytest-4.0. It is recommended to pass a list of "
"arguments instead (`#1723`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2857
msgid ""
"Rename ``getfuncargvalue`` to ``getfixturevalue``. ``getfuncargvalue`` is "
"still present but is now considered deprecated. Thanks to `@RedBeardCode`_ "
"and `@tomviner`_ for the PR (`#1626`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2861
msgid "``optparse`` type usage now triggers DeprecationWarnings (`#1740`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2864
msgid ""
"``optparse`` backward compatibility supports float/complex types (`#457`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2866
msgid ""
"Refined logic for determining the ``rootdir``, considering only valid paths "
"which fixes a number of issues: `#1594`_, `#1435`_ and `#1471`_. Updated the "
"documentation according to current behavior. Thanks to `@blueyed`_, "
"`@davehunt`_ and `@matthiasha`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2871
msgid ""
"Always include full assertion explanation. The previous behaviour was hiding "
"sub-expressions that happened to be False, assuming this was redundant "
"information. Thanks `@bagerard`_ for reporting (`#1503`_). Thanks to "
"`@davehunt`_ and `@tomviner`_ for PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2876
msgid ""
"Better message in case of not using parametrized variable (see `#1539`_). "
"Thanks to `@tramwaj29`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2879
msgid "Updated docstrings with a more uniform style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2881
msgid ""
"Add stderr write for ``pytest.exit(msg)`` during startup. Previously the "
"message was never shown. Thanks `@BeyondEvil`_ for reporting `#1210`_. "
"Thanks to `@JonathonSonesen`_ and `@tomviner`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2885
msgid ""
"No longer display the incorrect test deselection reason (`#1372`_). Thanks "
"`@ronnypfannschmidt`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2888
msgid ""
"The ``--resultlog`` command line option has been deprecated: it is little "
"used and there are more modern and better alternatives (see `#830`_). Thanks "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2892
msgid ""
"Improve error message with fixture lookup errors: add an 'E' to the first "
"line and '>' to the rest. Fixes `#717`_. Thanks `@blueyed`_ for reporting "
"and a PR, `@eolo999`_ for the initial PR and `@tomviner`_ for his guidance "
"during EuroPython2016 sprint."
msgstr ""

