#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3055
msgid ""
"Fix maximum recursion depth detection when raised error class is not aware "
"of unicode/encoded bytes. Thanks `@prusse-martin`_ for the PR (`#1506`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3059
msgid ""
"Fix ``pytest.mark.skip`` mark when used in strict mode. Thanks `@pquentin`_ "
"for the PR and `@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for showing how to fix the bug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3063
msgid ""
"Minor improvements and fixes to the documentation. Thanks `@omarkohl`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3066
msgid ""
"Fix ``--fixtures`` to show all fixture definitions as opposed to just one "
"per fixture name. Thanks to `@hackebrot`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3080
msgid "2.9.1 (2016-03-17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3084
msgid ""
"Improve error message when a plugin fails to load. Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3087
msgid ""
"Fix (`#1178 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1178>`_): ``pytest."
"fail`` with non-ascii characters raises an internal pytest error. Thanks "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3091
msgid ""
"Fix (`#469`_): junit parses report.nodeid incorrectly, when params IDs "
"contain ``::``. Thanks `@tomviner`_ for the PR (`#1431`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3094
msgid ""
"Fix (`#578 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/578>`_): "
"SyntaxErrors containing non-ascii lines at the point of failure generated an "
"internal py.test error. Thanks `@asottile`_ for the report and "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3099
msgid ""
"Fix (`#1437`_): When passing in a bytestring regex pattern to parameterize "
"attempt to decode it as utf-8 ignoring errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3102
msgid ""
"Fix (`#649`_): parametrized test nodes cannot be specified to run on the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3104
msgid "Fix (`#138`_): better reporting for python 3.3+ chained exceptions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3116
msgid "2.9.0 (2016-02-29)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3120
msgid ""
"New ``pytest.mark.skip`` mark, which unconditionally skips marked tests. "
"Thanks `@MichaelAquilina`_ for the complete PR (`#1040`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3123
msgid ""
"``--doctest-glob`` may now be passed multiple times in the command-line. "
"Thanks `@jab`_ and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3126
msgid ""
"New ``-rp`` and ``-rP`` reporting options give the summary and full output "
"of passing tests, respectively. Thanks to `@codewarrior0`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3129
msgid ""
"``pytest.mark.xfail`` now has a ``strict`` option, which makes ``XPASS`` "
"tests to fail the test suite (defaulting to ``False``). There's also a "
"``xfail_strict`` ini option that can be used to configure it project-wise. "
"Thanks `@rabbbit`_ for the request and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR (`#1355`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3134
msgid ""
"``Parser.addini`` now supports options of type ``bool``. Thanks "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3137
msgid ""
"New ``ALLOW_BYTES`` doctest option. This strips ``b`` prefixes from byte "
"strings in doctest output (similar to ``ALLOW_UNICODE``). Thanks `@jaraco`_ "
"for the request and `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR (`#1287`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3141
msgid ""
"Give a hint on ``KeyboardInterrupt`` to use the ``--fulltrace`` option to "
"show the errors. Fixes `#1366`_. Thanks to `@hpk42`_ for the report and "
"`@RonnyPfannschmidt`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3145
msgid ""
"Catch ``IndexError`` exceptions when getting exception source location. "
"Fixes a pytest internal error for dynamically generated code (fixtures and "
"tests) where source lines are fake by intention."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3151
msgid ""
"**Important**: `py.code <https://pylib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/code.html>`_ "
"has been merged into the ``pytest`` repository as ``pytest._code``. This "
"decision was made because ``py.code`` had very few uses outside ``pytest`` "
"and the fact that it was in a different repository made it difficult to fix "
"bugs on its code in a timely manner. The team hopes with this to be able to "
"better refactor out and improve that code. This change shouldn't affect "
"users, but it is useful to let users aware if they encounter any strange "
"behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3160
msgid ""
"Keep in mind that the code for ``pytest._code`` is **private** and "
"**experimental**, so you definitely should not import it explicitly!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3163
msgid ""
"Please note that the original ``py.code`` is still available in `pylib "
"<https://pylib.readthedocs.io>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3166
msgid ""
"``pytest_enter_pdb`` now optionally receives the pytest config object. "
"Thanks `@nicoddemus`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3169
msgid ""
"Removed code and documentation for Python 2.5 or lower versions, including "
"removal of the obsolete ``_pytest.assertion.oldinterpret`` module. Thanks "
"`@nicoddemus`_ for the PR (`#1226`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3173
msgid ""
"Comparisons now always show up in full when ``CI`` or ``BUILD_NUMBER`` is "
"found in the environment, even when ``-vv`` isn't used. Thanks `@The-"
"Compiler`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3177
msgid ""
"``--lf`` and ``--ff`` now support long names: ``--last-failed`` and ``--"
"failed-first`` respectively. Thanks `@MichaelAquilina`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3181
msgid "Added expected exceptions to ``pytest.raises`` fail message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3183
msgid ""
"Collection only displays progress (\"collecting X items\") when in a "
"terminal. This avoids cluttering the output when using ``--color=yes`` to "
"obtain colors in CI integrations systems (`#1397`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3189
msgid ""
"The ``-s`` and ``-c`` options should now work under ``xdist``; ``Config."
"fromdictargs`` now represents its input much more faithfully. Thanks to "
"`@bukzor`_ for the complete PR (`#680`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3193
msgid ""
"Fix (`#1290`_): support Python 3.5's ``@`` operator in assertion rewriting. "
"Thanks `@Shinkenjoe`_ for report with test case and `@tomviner`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3196
msgid ""
"Fix formatting utf-8 explanation messages (`#1379`_). Thanks `@biern`_ for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3199
msgid ""
"Fix `traceback style docs`_ to describe all of the available options (auto/"
"long/short/line/native/no), with ``auto`` being the default since v2.6. "
"Thanks `@hackebrot`_ for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3203
msgid ""
"Fix (`#1422`_): junit record_xml_property doesn't allow multiple records "
"with same name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3237
msgid "2.8.7 (2016-01-24)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3239
msgid "fix #1338: use predictable object resolution for monkeypatch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3242
msgid "2.8.6 (2016-01-21)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3244
msgid ""
"fix #1259: allow for double nodeids in junitxml, this was a regression "
"failing plugins combinations like pytest-pep8 + pytest-flakes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3248
msgid ""
"Workaround for exception that occurs in pyreadline when using ``--pdb`` with "
"standard I/O capture enabled. Thanks Erik M. Bray for the PR."
msgstr ""

