#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3702
msgid "2.7.0 (2015-03-26)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3704
msgid ""
"fix issue435: make reload() work when assert rewriting is active. Thanks "
"Daniel Hahler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3707
msgid ""
"fix issue616: conftest.py files and their contained fixutres are now "
"properly considered for visibility, independently from the exact current "
"working directory and test arguments that are used. Many thanks to Eric "
"Siegerman and his PR235 which contains systematic tests for conftest "
"visibility and now passes. This change also introduces the concept of a "
"``rootdir`` which is printed as a new pytest header and documented in the "
"pytest customize web page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3716
msgid ""
"change reporting of \"diverted\" tests, i.e. tests that are collected in one "
"file but actually come from another (e.g. when tests in a test class come "
"from a base class in a different file).  We now show the nodeid and indicate "
"via a postfix the other file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3721
msgid ""
"add ability to set command line options by environment variable "
"PYTEST_ADDOPTS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3723
msgid ""
"added documentation on the new pytest-dev teams on bitbucket and github.  "
"See https://pytest.org/latest/contributing.html . Thanks to Anatoly for "
"pushing and initial work on this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3727
msgid ""
"fix issue650: new option ``--docttest-ignore-import-errors`` which will turn "
"import errors in doctests into skips.  Thanks Charles Cloud for the complete "
"PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3731
msgid ""
"fix issue655: work around different ways that cause python2/3 to leak sys."
"exc_info into fixtures/tests causing failures in 3rd party code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3734
msgid ""
"fix issue615: assertion rewriting did not correctly escape % signs when "
"formatting boolean operations, which tripped over mixing booleans with "
"modulo operators.  Thanks to Tom Viner for the report, triaging and fix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3739
msgid ""
"implement issue351: add ability to specify parametrize ids as a callable to "
"generate custom test ids.  Thanks Brianna Laugher for the idea and "
"implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3743
msgid ""
"introduce and document new hookwrapper mechanism useful for plugins which "
"want to wrap the execution of certain hooks for their purposes. This "
"supersedes the undocumented ``__multicall__`` protocol which pytest itself "
"and some external plugins use.  Note that pytest-2.8 is scheduled to drop "
"supporting the old ``__multicall__`` and only support the hookwrapper "
"protocol."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3750
msgid "majorly speed up invocation of plugin hooks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3752
msgid "use hookwrapper mechanism in builtin pytest plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3754
msgid "add a doctest ini option for doctest flags, thanks Holger Peters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3756
msgid ""
"add note to docs that if you want to mark a parameter and the parameter is a "
"callable, you also need to pass in a reason to disambiguate it from the "
"\"decorator\" case.  Thanks Tom Viner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3760
msgid ""
"\"python_classes\" and \"python_functions\" options now support glob-"
"patterns for test discovery, as discussed in issue600. Thanks Ldiary "
"Translations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3763
msgid ""
"allow to override parametrized fixtures with non-parametrized ones and vice "
"versa (bubenkoff)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3765
msgid ""
"fix issue463: raise specific error for 'parameterize' misspelling "
"(pfctdayelise)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3767
msgid ""
"On failure, the ``sys.last_value``, ``sys.last_type`` and ``sys."
"last_traceback`` are set, so that a user can inspect the error via "
"postmortem debugging (almarklein)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3772
msgid "2.6.4 (2014-10-24)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3774
msgid ""
"Improve assertion failure reporting on iterables, by using ndiff and pprint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3777
msgid "removed outdated japanese docs from source tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3779
msgid "docs for \"pytest_addhooks\" hook.  Thanks Bruno Oliveira."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3781
msgid "updated plugin index docs.  Thanks Bruno Oliveira."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3783
msgid ""
"fix issue557: with \"-k\" we only allow the old style \"-\" for negation at "
"the beginning of strings and even that is deprecated.  Use \"not\" instead. "
"This should allow to pick parametrized tests where \"-\" appeared in the "
"parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3787
msgid "fix issue604: Escape % character in the assertion message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3789 ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3795
msgid ""
"fix issue620: add explanation in the --genscript target about what the "
"binary blob means. Thanks Dinu Gherman."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3792 ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3798
msgid "fix issue614: fixed pastebin support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3801
msgid "2.6.3 (2014-09-24)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3803
msgid ""
"fix issue575: xunit-xml was reporting collection errors as failures instead "
"of errors, thanks Oleg Sinyavskiy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3806
msgid ""
"fix issue582: fix setuptools example, thanks Laszlo Papp and Ronny "
