"Thanks Charles Cloud for analysing the issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3817
msgid ""
"fix conftest related fixture visibility issue: when running with a CWD "
"outside of a test package pytest would get fixture discovery wrong. Thanks "
"to Wolfgang Schnerring for figuring out a reproducible example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3821
msgid ""
"Introduce pytest_enter_pdb hook (needed e.g. by pytest_timeout to cancel the "
"timeout when interactively entering pdb).  Thanks Wolfgang Schnerring."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3824
msgid ""
"check xfail/skip also with non-python function test items. Thanks Floris "
"Bruynooghe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3828
msgid "2.6.2 (2014-09-05)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3830
msgid ""
"Added function pytest.freeze_includes(), which makes it easy to embed pytest "
"into executables using tools like cx_freeze. See docs for examples and "
"rationale. Thanks Bruno Oliveira."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3834
msgid "Improve assertion rewriting cache invalidation precision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3836
msgid "fixed issue561: adapt autouse fixture example for python3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3838
msgid ""
"fixed issue453: assertion rewriting issue with __repr__ containing \"\\n{\", "
"\"\\n}\" and \"\\n~\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3841
msgid ""
"fix issue560: correctly display code if an \"else:\" or \"finally:\" is "
"followed by statements on the same line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3844
msgid "Fix example in monkeypatch documentation, thanks t-8ch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3846
msgid "fix issue572: correct tmpdir doc example for python3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3848
msgid ""
"Do not mark as universal wheel because Python 2.6 is different from other "
"builds due to the extra argparse dependency.  Fixes issue566. Thanks sontek."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3852
msgid ""
"Implement issue549: user-provided assertion messages now no longer replace "
"the py.test introspection message but are shown in addition to them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3857
msgid "2.6.1 (2014-08-07)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3859
msgid ""
"No longer show line numbers in the --verbose output, the output is now "
"purely the nodeid.  The line number is still shown in failure reports. "
"Thanks Floris Bruynooghe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3863
msgid ""
"fix issue437 where assertion rewriting could cause pytest-xdist slaves to "
"collect different tests. Thanks Bruno Oliveira."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3866
msgid ""
"fix issue555: add \"errors\" attribute to capture-streams to satisfy some "
"distutils and possibly other code accessing sys.stdout.errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3869
msgid ""
"fix issue547 capsys/capfd also work when output capturing (\"-s\") is "
"disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3871
msgid ""
"address issue170: allow pytest.mark.xfail(...) to specify expected "
"exceptions via an optional \"raises=EXC\" argument where EXC can be a single "
"exception or a tuple of exception classes.  Thanks David Mohr for the "
"complete PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3876
msgid ""
"fix integration of pytest with unittest.mock.patch decorator when it uses "
"the \"new\" argument.  Thanks Nicolas Delaby for test and PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3879
msgid ""
"fix issue with detecting conftest files if the arguments contain \"::\" node "
"id specifications (copy pasted from \"-v\" output)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3882
msgid ""
"fix issue544 by only removing \"@NUM\" at the end of \"::\" separated parts "
"and if the part has a \".py\" extension"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3885
msgid ""
"don't use py.std import helper, rather import things directly. Thanks Bruno "
"Oliveira."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3889
msgid "2.6"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3891
msgid "Cache exceptions from fixtures according to their scope (issue 467)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3893
msgid ""
"fix issue537: Avoid importing old assertion reinterpretation code by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3895
msgid ""
"fix issue364: shorten and enhance tracebacks representation by default. The "
"new \"--tb=auto\" option (default) will only display long tracebacks for the "
"first and last entry.  You can get the old behaviour of printing all entries "
"as long entries with \"--tb=long\".  Also short entries by default are now "
"printed very similarly to \"--tb=native\" ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3901
msgid ""
"fix issue514: teach assertion reinterpretation about private class attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3903
msgid ""
"change -v output to include full node IDs of tests.  Users can copy a node "
"ID from a test run, including line number, and use it as a positional "
"argument in order to run only a single test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3907
msgid ""
"fix issue 475: fail early and comprehensible if calling pytest.raises with "
"wrong exception type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3910
msgid "fix issue516: tell in getting-started about current dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3912
msgid ""
"cleanup setup.py a bit and specify supported versions. Thanks Jurko "
"Gospodnetic for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3915
msgid ""
"change XPASS colour to yellow rather then red when tests are run with -v."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3918
msgid ""
"fix issue473: work around mock putting an unbound method into a class dict "
"when double-patching."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3921
msgid ""
"fix issue498: if a fixture finalizer fails, make sure that the fixture is "
"still invalidated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3924
msgid ""
"fix issue453: the result of the pytest_assertrepr_compare hook now gets it's "
"newlines escaped so that format_exception does not blow up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3927
msgid ""
"internal new warning system: pytest will now produce warnings when it "
"detects oddities in your test collection or execution. Warnings are "
"ultimately sent to a new pytest_logwarning hook which is currently only "
"implemented by the terminal plugin which displays warnings in the summary "
"line and shows more details when -rw (report on warnings) is specified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3934
msgid ""
"change skips into warnings for test classes with an __init__ and callables "
"in test modules which look like a test but are not functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3937
msgid ""
"fix issue436: improved finding of initial conftest files from command line "
"arguments by using the result of parse_known_args rather than the previous "
"flaky heuristics.  Thanks Marc Abramowitz for tests and initial fixing "
"approaches in this area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3942
msgid ""
"fix issue #479: properly handle nose/unittest(2) SkipTest exceptions during "
"collection/loading of test modules.  Thanks to Marc Schlaich for the "
"complete PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3946
msgid ""
"fix issue490: include pytest_load_initial_conftests in documentation and "
"improve docstring."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3949
msgid ""
"fix issue472: clarify that ``pytest.config.getvalue()`` cannot work if it's "
"triggered ahead of command line parsing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3952
msgid "merge PR123: improved integration with mock.patch decorator on tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3954
msgid ""
"fix issue412: messing with stdout/stderr FD-level streams is now captured "
"without crashes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3957
msgid ""
"fix issue483: trial/py33 works now properly.  Thanks Daniel Grana for PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3959
msgid ""
"improve example for pytest integration with \"python setup.py test\" which "
"now has a generic \"-a\" or \"--pytest-args\" option where you can pass "
"additional options as a quoted string.  Thanks Trevor Bekolay."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3963
msgid ""
"simplified internal capturing mechanism and made it more robust against "
"tests or setups changing FD1/FD2, also better integrated now with pytest."
"pdb() in single tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3967
msgid ""
"improvements to pytest's own test-suite leakage detection, courtesy of PRs "
"from Marc Abramowitz"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3970
msgid "fix issue492: avoid leak in test_writeorg.  Thanks Marc Abramowitz."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3972
msgid ""
"fix issue493: don't run tests in doc directory with ``python setup.py test`` "
"(use tox -e doctesting for that)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3975
msgid ""
"fix issue486: better reporting and handling of early conftest loading "
"failures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3977
msgid "some cleanup and simplification of internal conftest handling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3979
msgid ""
"work a bit harder to break reference cycles when catching exceptions. Thanks "
"Jurko Gospodnetic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3982
msgid ""
"fix issue443: fix skip examples to use proper comparison.  Thanks Alex "
"Groenholm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3985
msgid ""
"support nose-style ``__test__`` attribute on modules, classes and functions, "
"including unittest-style Classes.  If set to False, the test will not be "
"collected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3989
msgid ""
"fix issue512: show \"<notset>\" for arguments which might not be set in "
"monkeypatch plugin.  Improves output in documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3994
msgid "2.5.2 (2014-01-29)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3996
msgid ""
"fix issue409 -- better interoperate with cx_freeze by not trying to import "
"from collections.abc which causes problems for py27/cx_freeze.  Thanks "
"Wolfgang L. for reporting and tracking it down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4000
msgid ""
"fixed docs and code to use \"pytest\" instead of \"py.test\" almost "
"everywhere. Thanks Jurko Gospodnetic for the complete PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4003
msgid ""
"fix issue425: mention at end of \"py.test -h\" that --markers and --fixtures "
"work according to specified test path (or current dir)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4006
msgid ""
"fix issue413: exceptions with unicode attributes are now printed correctly "
"also on python2 and with pytest-xdist runs. (the fix requires py-1.4.20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4010
msgid ""
"copy, cleanup and integrate py.io capture from pylib 1.4.20.dev2 (rev "
"13d9af95547e)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4013
msgid "address issue416: clarify docs as to conftest.py loading semantics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4015
msgid ""
"fix issue429: comparing byte strings with non-ascii chars in assert "
"expressions now work better.  Thanks Floris Bruynooghe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4018
msgid "make capfd/capsys.capture private, its unused and shouldn't be exposed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4022
msgid "2.5.1 (2013-12-17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4024
msgid "merge new documentation styling PR from Tobias Bieniek."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4026
msgid ""
"fix issue403: allow parametrize of multiple same-name functions within a "
"collection node.  Thanks Andreas Kloeckner and Alex Gaynor for reporting and "
"analysis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4030
msgid ""
"Allow parameterized fixtures to specify the ID of the parameters by adding "
"an ids argument to pytest.fixture() and pytest.yield_fixture(). Thanks "
"Floris Bruynooghe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4034
msgid ""
"fix issue404 by always using the binary xml escape in the junitxml plugin.  "
"Thanks Ronny Pfannschmidt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4037
msgid ""
"fix issue407: fix addoption docstring to point to argparse instead of "
"optparse. Thanks Daniel D. Wright."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4043
msgid "2.5.0 (2013-12-12)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4045
msgid ""
"dropped python2.5 from automated release testing of pytest itself which "
"means it's probably going to break soon (but still works with this release "
"we believe)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4049
msgid ""
"simplified and fixed implementation for calling finalizers when parametrized "
"fixtures or function arguments are involved.  finalization is now performed "
"lazily at setup time instead of in the \"teardown phase\". While this might "
"sound odd at first, it helps to ensure that we are correctly handling setup/"
"teardown even in complex code.  User-level code should not be affected "
"unless it's implementing the pytest_runtest_teardown hook and expecting "
"certain fixture instances are torn down within (very unlikely and would have "
"been unreliable anyway)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4058
msgid ""
"PR90: add --color=yes|no|auto option to force terminal coloring mode "
"(\"auto\" is default).  Thanks Marc Abramowitz."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4061
msgid ""
"fix issue319 - correctly show unicode in assertion errors.  Many thanks to "
"Floris Bruynooghe for the complete PR.  Also means we depend on py>=1.4.19 "
"now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4065
msgid ""
"fix issue396 - correctly sort and finalize class-scoped parametrized tests "
"independently from number of methods on the class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4068
msgid ""
"refix issue323 in a better way -- parametrization should now never cause "
"Runtime Recursion errors because the underlying algorithm for re-ordering "
"tests per-scope/per-fixture is not recursive anymore (it was tail-call "
"recursive before which could lead to problems for more than >966 non-"
"function scoped parameters)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4074
msgid ""
"fix issue290 - there is preliminary support now for parametrizing with "
"repeated same values (sometimes useful to test if calling a second time "
"works as with the first time)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4078
msgid ""
"close issue240 - document precisely how pytest module importing works, "
"discuss the two common test directory layouts, and how it interacts with "
"PEP420-namespace packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4082
msgid ""
"fix issue246 fix finalizer order to be LIFO on independent fixtures "
"depending on a parametrized higher-than-function scoped fixture. (was quite "
"some effort so please bear with the complexity of this sentence :) Thanks "
"Ralph Schmitt for the precise failure example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4087
msgid ""
"fix issue244 by implementing special index for parameters to only use "
"indices for paramentrized test ids"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4090
msgid ""
"fix issue287 by running all finalizers but saving the exception from the "
"first failing finalizer and re-raising it so teardown will still have "
"failed.  We reraise the first failing exception because it might be the "
"cause for other finalizers to fail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4095
msgid ""
"fix ordering when mock.patch or other standard decorator-wrappings are used "
"with test methods.  This fixues issue346 and should help with random "
"\"xdist\" collection failures.  Thanks to Ronny Pfannschmidt and Donald "
"Stufft for helping to isolate it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4100
msgid ""
"fix issue357 - special case \"-k\" expressions to allow for filtering with "
"simple strings that are not valid python expressions. Examples: \"-k 1.3\" "
"matches all tests parametrized with 1.3. \"-k None\" filters all tests that "
"have \"None\" in their name and conversely \"-k 'not None'\". Previously "
"these examples would raise syntax errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4107
msgid ""
"fix issue384 by removing the trial support code since the unittest compat "
"enhancements allow trial to handle it on its own"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4111
msgid ""
"don't hide an ImportError when importing a plugin produces one. fixes "
"issue375."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4114
msgid ""
"fix issue275 - allow usefixtures and autouse fixtures for running doctest "
"text files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4117
msgid ""
"fix issue380 by making --resultlog only rely on longrepr instead of the "
"\"reprcrash\" attribute which only exists sometimes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4120
msgid ""
"address issue122: allow @pytest.fixture(params=iterator) by exploding into a "
"list early on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4123
msgid "fix pexpect-3.0 compatibility for pytest's own tests. (fixes issue386)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4126
msgid "allow nested parametrize-value markers, thanks James Lan for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4128
msgid ""
"fix unicode handling with new monkeypatch.setattr(import_path, value) API.  "
"Thanks Rob Dennis.  Fixes issue371."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4131
msgid "fix unicode handling with junitxml, fixes issue368."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4133
msgid ""
"In assertion rewriting mode on Python 2, fix the detection of coding "
"cookies. See issue #330."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4136
msgid ""
"make \"--runxfail\" turn imperative pytest.xfail calls into no ops (it "
"already did neutralize pytest.mark.xfail markers)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4139
msgid ""
"refine pytest / pkg_resources interactions: The AssertionRewritingHook "
"PEP302 compliant loader now registers itself with setuptools/pkg_resources "
"properly so that the pkg_resources.resource_stream method works properly. "
"Fixes issue366.  Thanks for the investigations and full PR to Jason R. "
"Coombs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4144
msgid ""
"pytestconfig fixture is now session-scoped as it is the same object during "
"the whole test run.  Fixes issue370."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4147
msgid "avoid one surprising case of marker malfunction/confusion::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4149
msgid ""
"@pytest.mark.some(lambda arg: ...)\n"
"def test_function():"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4152
msgid ""
"would not work correctly because pytest assumes @pytest.mark.some gets a "
"function to be decorated already.  We now at least detect if this arg is a "
"lambda and thus the example will work.  Thanks Alex Gaynor for bringing it "
"up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4157
msgid ""
"xfail a test on pypy that checks wrong encoding/ascii (pypy does not error "
"out). fixes issue385."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CHANGELOG.rst:4160
msgid ""
"internally make varnames() deal with classes's __init__, although it's not "
"needed by pytest itself atm.  Also fix caching.  Fixes issue376."
msgstr ""

